radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is distended up to 8-9 mm with wall thickening and surrounding fat stranding. No focal fluid collections or extraluminal gas identified. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Other abdominal organs (liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, urinary bladder, reproductive organs) are unremarkable. Some prominent reactive ileocecal lymph nodes seen. No retroperitoneal, pelvic, or inguinal lymphadenopathy. No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
